body:
A fix that works for me is to override the `evaludateAttributes` method and skips calling parent one when it is beforeUpdate event with no dirty attributes:

``` php
    public function evaluateAttributes($event)
    {
        if ($event->name === BaseActiveRecord::EVENT_BEFORE_UPDATE &&
                empty($this->owner->getDirtyAttributes())) {
            return;
        }
        parent::evaluateAttributes($event);
    }
```
